Q4/- What is a Race condition, How will you solve the Race condition,explain with an
Example.

Answer- 

--The concept of avoiding multiple threads acting upon the same functionality simultaneously
is known as Thread-safety.
--Concurrency issue lead to the Rac-condition and race-condition lead to data inconsistency.

--Race-condition can be defined as a condition in which two or more threads compete
together to get certain shared resources.

--To solve the data inconsistency problem in java *synchronized* keyword is used.
--so the thread-safety is achieved and race-condition is avoided by the help of synchronized
keyword.

Exanple- refer Common.java, ThreadA.java, ThreadB.java and Main.java.